The DVD's of Fresh Prince I bought for my fianc are perfect! They are in great shape!! Seem to be brand new. The packing was tight and the DVD's were still sealed. SUCH a great show! If your hesitation for buying these is worry over whether there in good condition, I hope to put your mind at rest. They were flawless.

If, however, your hesitation is whether or not you want to try this show, I GUARANTEE that this is a must watch! I can't imagine that there is someone out there that has never seen this show, but I promise that it will become your favorite show. Not only is it family-friendly entertainment, but Fresh Prince has a great plot line and outstanding comedy.

Well, actually, through a couple of things I learned about the Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, then I heard the theme song and I liked it, so I watched the first episode and it was AMAZING, so I watched the second episode. I did not expect them to be rich, so that was a big surprise to me. I mean, I didn't know what Bel-Air was or where Bel-Air was. The main character is very good at singing and rapping but he does it in the most immature way. He just copied the dance moves of the younger sisters dancing, and if you can just copy the moves after a few seconds, thats impressive.

For the most part this is obviously a great show so I am not complaining about that at all. Unfortunately the second season has an error, the first and second discs are identical, like the label printed was an error, I didn't realize this until after the return deadline as I didn't watch it fast enough. So I kinda got screwed out of and entire disc of episodes.

I don't know if anyone else has this issue, but on the second season box of my set, disc 1 is just a duplicate of disc 2. the CDs LOOK different, but the content is the same; both contain Episodes 7-12; 1-6 are missing for me. I even put them in many times to compare the menu options on the DVDs. I got this as a gift so I can't return it, but I'm really unhappy about missing 6 episodes and have 2 of the same thing.

Oh my. I made the mistake of reading reviews for this after I made the purchase. Season 1: Two DVDs wouldn't play. Season 2: Discs 1 and 2 both played disc 2 material, disc 3 played disc 4 material, and disc 4 played disc 1 material. I would have been okay with everything being mixed up had all disc material been present, but I am missing all episodes from disc 3. I don't understand how something like this could be so incredibly messed up; it was cheap enough that I won't bother sending it back, but the cheap price was not worth buying on the first price.

I opened season 1 and began to watch. There is an episode guide inside the box and there are more episodes listed than episodes that are listed on episode guide on the second DVD of the first season. I believe it was missing at least 3 episodes. I didn't bother opening season 2 because I wanted to return set and who know how many would be missing from that. Even if it's just one missing or none from that season it's not worth it to me. I'd rather pay a couple dollars more to get all episodes that belong on these seasons. They are also put in case in a cheap manner. They are just stacked in one DVD touching the next to fit in smaller box. Makes it easier to scratch them the way it's stored. At least amazon is good about customer service so I was able to return for a refund. The part that bothers me with anything I put money into is when you pay for something expecting one thing based on way it's advertised and it arrives missing something, damaged or seller just left something out. I will be leaving seller review to and if other seasons from other sellers come complete I will be adding positive review to them and on product page because if this was right would be a great item to have. Hope this helps someone.

I forgot just how silly this show was! When I was younger it was one of my favorites and I couldn't wait until it was going to be on. You can definitely see (especially in some of the more serious moments in the show)  why Will Smith has become the great actor he is today. It's great to hear the slang used that I had totally forgotten about!! The 90's were a great time!! If you liked the show then, I'm sure you'll still like it now! The price was great too! $19.99 for 2 seasons!! The DVD' s are in great shape as well as the cases. Definitely worth the money!! I'm not disappointed one bit.
This came as a low price double set. I am sure looking forward to watching the young Will Smith strut his silly stuff! Great family series from the 90's. Sets arrived inperfect condition, thank you!
